article.headline: Delaware 72, Hofstra 68
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Brian Johnson scored a game-high 25 points, Herb Courtney contributed 22 points, and Delaware defeated Hofstra 72-68 Monday night. The Blue Hens (4-18, 2-9 CAA) rallied from a seven-point deficit at halftime, and got a three pointer from Sam McMahon and two free throws from Darrell Johnson in the last 11 seconds to win. Johnson landed five of Delaware's 12 three-pointers and had four assists as Delaware ended a four-game losing streak. Chris Gadley grabbed a team-high 11 rebounds. Loren Stokes led the Pride (16-6, 9-2 CAA) with 21 points while Antoine Agudio added 19 points and Zygis Sestokas contributed 11 points. Chris Gadley had a game-high 11 rebounds.
